{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/covid-19-and-the-future-of-data-privacy-54c49f64387c", "time": 1683005661.590192, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/covid-19-and-the-future-of-data-privacy-54c49f64387c/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "COVID-19 and the future of Data Privacy | by David Pereira | Towards Data Science", "h1": "COVID-19 and the future of Data Privacy", "description": "The March 28th edition of the Official Spanish Bulletin (BOE, Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado) of March 28 confirmed it: The Spanish government had entrusted the Secretary of State for Digitization and\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/2020/03/28/pdfs/BOE-A-2020-4162.pdf", "anchor_text": "The March 28th edition of the Official Spanish Bulletin", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/IMG/pdf/comparaisonUE_EU_data", "anchor_text": "feeding comparisons between European and American liberty and privacy", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://edpb.europa.eu/sites/edpb/files/files/file1/edpb_statement_2020_processingpersonaldataandcovid-19_en.pdf", "anchor_text": "its statement", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://www.aepd.es/es/prensa-y-comunicacion/notas-de-prensa/la-aepd-publica-un-informe-sobre-los-tratamientos-de-datos-en", "anchor_text": "also spoke on this matter", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/manuelabat/status/1241250617005309952?s=20", "anchor_text": "sent the government a letter", "paragraph_index": 5}, {"url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/24/technology/europe-gdpr-privacy.html", "anchor_text": "Europe is considered to be leading the defense of data privacy", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://dpereirapaz.medium.com/membership", "anchor_text": "consider a membership", "paragraph_index": 10}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dpereirapaz/", "anchor_text": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dpereirapaz/", "paragraph_index": 12}], "all_paragraphs": ["The March 28th edition of the Official Spanish Bulletin (BOE, Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado) of March 28 confirmed it: The Spanish government had entrusted the Secretary of State for Digitization and Artificial Intelligence (SEDIA) with the urgent development of a computer application to support the management of the health crisis caused by COVID-19.", "Among the functionalities of the application is the possibility of geolocating the user in order to verify declared location. With this, the debate was opened: Should an emergency situation like the current one prevail over the privacy rights of citizens\u2019 data?", "Comparisons with the Chinese surveillance model were swift. Both from the point of view of the measure\u2019s effectiveness, and from the point of view of the deprivation of liberty and privacy of citizens. Some other countries like the USA have also previously used surveillance and data mining under sensitive national security arguments like the war on terror, feeding comparisons between European and American liberty and privacy. Is a model like the Chinese translatable in Europe? Under what conditions?", "The European Data Protection Board (EDPB) was already discussing this topic a few days ago. In its statement, entitled \u201cOn the processing of personal data in the context of the COVID-19 outbreak\u201d, this body already recognized that \u201cGDPR (General Data Protection Regulation) provides for the legal grounds to enable the employers and the competent public health authorities to process personal data in the context of epidemics, without the need to obtain the consent of the data subject\u201d that is, GDPR allows authorities and employers to process personal data in an epidemic context without the subject\u2019s explicit consent. The statement points out that the use of data related to digital communications, such as the location of a mobile device, can only be used when the content is anonymized, although it opens the door for states to legislate when this is not possible and always subject to measures related to public health or safety.", "The Spanish Data Protection Agency (AEPD) also spoke on this matter, stating that \u201cdata protection should not be used to hinder or limit the effectiveness of the measures adopted by the authorities, especially health authorities.\u201d", "A series of Spanish lawyers, researchers, academics, and other experts are concerned about this issue and sent the government a letter a few days ago in which they promoted the legal, ethical and transparent management of citizens\u2019 data.", "The authors of the paper emphasize above all the relevant role that technology and the use of data can play in alleviating this emergency situation, but they warn of two major risks:", "In short, technology, and specifically techniques applied to big data and AI, must be at the service of people and society. For this, key mechanisms are going to be transparency and its ethical use, including topics such as bias control or identity protection, for example.", "Without a doubt, the protection of our private data is a fundamental right and it is at times like this that a society must find the difficult balance between this right and the public interest. Europe is considered to be leading the defense of data privacy, specially when it comes to the use of technology since GDPR (2018). However, as the experts are warning us in the above mentioned letter, how we manage this health crisis can not only affect our health or economy, but perhaps also on the degree of control that governments will be able to exercise through the use of technology.", "Exceptional situations require exceptional measures, but, as the EDPB declaration itself indicates, always under conditions of necessity and proportionality in a democratic society.", "If you enjoyed reading this piece, please consider a membership to get full access to every story while supporting me and other writers on Medium.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Data & Intelligence Partner at NTT DATA Europe & Latam. All opinions are my own. https://www.linkedin.com/in/dpereirapaz/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F54c49f64387c&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcovid-19-and-the-future-of-data-privacy-54c49f64387c&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcovid-19-and-the-future-of-data-privacy-54c49f64387c&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcovid-19-and-the-future-of-data-privacy-54c49f64387c&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcovid-19-and-the-future-of-data-privacy-54c49f64387c&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://towardsd